(288, 1, '2025-01-29 16:11:32', '2025-01-29 16:11:32', 'The flat bedded characteristic of Angus sandstone makes it ideal for cladding and is increasingly specified by many architects and clients. It is available in 100mm or 140mm depths and can be used as a traditional mortar build or as a dry effect build, (140mm only) where the mortar is back bedded. ', 'Guillotine Stone Cladding', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'guillotine-stone-cladding', '', '', '2025-02-23 18:59:35', '2025-02-23 18:59:35', '', 0, 'http://denfind/?post_type=products&#038;p=288', 4, 'products', '', 0),
(289, 1, '2025-01-29 16:12:03', '2025-01-29 16:12:03', 'These slips are an ideal cost-effective solution whilst using a Scottish product with the everlasting appeal that only natural stone can achieve. \r\n\r\nThe 40mm stone slips are natural stone slips that can be fixed onto the faade of a building or a wall. It is cut from Angus sandstone and once applied, gives the same appearance and effect as our 100mm and 140mm stone. It can be applied to either breeze block or a cement board. The 40mm stone is fixed to this using an adhesive and can be finished by pointing with mortar or left leaving a dry build effect. ', '40mm Cladding Slip', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', '40mm-cladding-slip', '', '', '2025-02-23 19:00:01', '2025-02-23 19:00:01', '', 0, 'http://denfind/?post_type=products&#038;p=289', 2, 'products', '', 0),
(290, 1, '2025-01-29 16:12:12', '2025-01-29 16:12:12', 'Flagstones were produced from Angus quarries and extensively used throughout the UK and worldwide in the 19th and early 20th centuries. Denfind Stone is continuing this legacy into the 21st century. \r\n\r\nFlagstones can be finished with either a sawn (smooth) or a riven (natural) finish and will normally be produced with sawn edges. Bespoke solutions are also available. ', 'Flagstones', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'flagstones', '', '', '2025-02-23 19:00:44', '2025-02-23 19:00:44', '', 0, 'http://denfind/?post_type=products&#038;p=290', 3, 'products', '', 0),
(291, 1, '2025-01-29 16:12:22', '2025-01-29 16:12:22', 'Angus sandstone is naturally flat bedded and ideal for dry stone dykes.\r\n\r\nAll dyking stone is handpicked to ensure the highest quality and that it is a manageable size for handling. Once picked, it is bagged to ensure that it is delivered to site as clean and dry as possible.', 'Dyking Stone', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'dyking-stone', '', '', '2025-02-23 19:01:18', '2025-02-23 19:01:18', '', 0, 'http://denfind/?post_type=products&#038;p=291', 1, 'products', '', 0),
(292, 1, '2025-01-29 16:12:32', '2025-01-29 16:12:32', 'These slips are an ideal cost-effective solution whilst using a Scottish product with the everlasting appeal that only natural stone can achieve.\r\n\r\n\r\nThe 40mm stone slips are natural stone slips that can be fixed onto the faade of a building or a wall. It is cut from Angus sandstone and once applied, gives the same appearance and effect as our 100mm and 140mm stone.', 'Coping Stones', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'coping-stones', '', '', '2025-03-28 06:19:38', '2025-03-28 06:19:38', '', 0, 'http://denfind/?post_type=products&#038;p=292', 0, 'products', '', 0),
(293, 1, '2025-01-29 16:12:38', '2025-01-29 16:12:38', 'Denfind Stone is an approved Scottish supplier of SureCav cavity spacer system. SureCav is a polypropylene panel that sits in the cavity and allows a stone outer skin to be built without the need for an additional block leaf. \r\n\r\nIt guarantees a clean 50mm, moisture free cavity that also arrests water penetration from wind driven rain in any exposed position and increases floor space by up to 5%, adding value to the project and reducing costs when compared to using concrete backing blocks. ', 'Surecav', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'surecav', '', '', '2025-02-23 19:02:05', '2025-02-23 19:02:05', '', 0, 'http://denfind/?post_type=products&#038;p=293', 5, 'products', '', 0),
(294, 1, '2025-01-29 16:12:46', '2025-01-29 16:12:46', 'Kerakoll H40 is the recommended mortar adhesive for use with our 40mm stone slips. It has been tested extensively both by Kerakoll and the University of Dundee with our stone and surpassed all trade standards for stone adhesives.', 'Kerakoll H40', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'kerakoll-h40', '', '', '2025-02-23 19:02:23', '2025-02-23 19:02:23', '', 0, 'http://denfind/?post_type=products&#038;p=294', 6, 'products', '', 0),
